From Welch Bryan Subject Re Changing oil by In article Grayson Walker writes Why crawl under the car at all I have a machine I got for my boat that pulls the oil out under suction through the dip stick It does an excellent job and by moving the suction tube around you can get more old oil out than by using the drain I think I paid at E B The oil goes into a steel gal can wait until it cools and decant into your favorite I use soft drink Easy to take them down to the local oil recycle This does sound good but I heard it tends to leave more grit etc in the oil Also I've been told to change the old when it's hot before the grit has much time to Any opinions Bryan Welch Amateur Radio Internet best Everything will perish save love and Scots Gaelic proverb Disclaimer It's all So